cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "AwesomeOPD: A Comprehensive Survey of On-Policy Distillation"
message: >-
  If you find this repository useful for your research,
  please cite it using the metadata from this file (or via
  the "Cite this repository" button on the GitHub page).
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: "Wei"
    family-names: "Liu"
    alias: "thinkwee"
  - name: "The AwesomeOPD Team"
abstract: >-
  AwesomeOPD is a curated, continuously updated list of open-source
  repositories and papers for training large language models (and VLMs,
  agents, and draft models) with On-Policy Distillation (OPD) and
  On-Policy Self-Distillation (OPSD). Each entry is annotated along four
  design axes — teacher source, supervision signal, rollout consumption,
  and pipeline slot — and organised into a taxonomy spanning surveys and
  foundations, white-box and black-box OPD, OPSD, iterative
  self-bootstrapping, OPD-RL hybrids, reasoning / multimodal / agent
  applications, speculative-decoding distillation, frameworks, and
  industrial production reports.
keywords:
  - "on-policy distillation"
  - "knowledge distillation"
  - "self-distillation"
  - "large language models"
  - "LLM"
  - "OPD"
  - "OPSD"
  - "speculative decoding"
  - "reinforcement learning"
  - "post-training"
  - "awesome list"
  - "machine learning"
repository-code: "https://github.com/thinkwee/AwesomeOPD"
url: "https://github.com/thinkwee/AwesomeOPD"
date-released: "2026-05-18"
